 <center><h2>Rune-Etched Armor (PoHate Drops)</h2><br><br>This set of armor is, for many shamans, the first set they will obtain.<br><br>All the pieces will drop reguarily off <a href='http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=1594'>Spite Golems</a> in the Plane of Hate, and each piece can be dropped by a different mob in the <a href='zones.php?zone=fear'>Plane of Fear</a>. Also in PoHate, the <a href='http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=6476'>Master of Spite</a> will randomly drop several pieces every time he is killed.<br><br>This set is fairly useful, because there are regularily pickup raids going to the Plane of Hate which you can join and roll on all drops. Or sometimes people will just be farming the zone and you can tag along and loot any shaman pieces (although some farmers will want to turn them in for a random gem, so you might want to offer to compensite this 100pp or so).<br><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=4877" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=4874" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=4872" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=4875" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=4876" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=4871" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=4873" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><br><br>This set is the closest upgrade to the <a href='index2.php?page=ldonarm2'>Geomancer's</a> armors, purchasable for 48 points a piece from Tak. The PoHate armor set is roughly on par with (slightly inferior to) the <a href='index2.php?page=augur'>Augur's</a> set which is reasonably easily questable on Luclin. Iksar Shamans have their own special set of PoHate armor which beats this: <a href='index2.php?page=poharmb'>Scaled Hierophant</a> armor.<br><br><br><br></center><br><u>Comments/Feedback:</u><br><br><form action='rate.php' method='post' name='rate'>
